    "\n",
    "## Part 1: Memory Kernels - A Comprehensive Study\n",
    "\n",
    "### The Memory Kernel K(t-œÑ)\n",
    "\n",
    "From Equation 18 in the paper:\n",
    "$$\\dot{\\rho}(t) = \\mathcal{L}[\\rho(t)] + \\int_0^t K(t-\\tau) \\rho(\\tau) d\\tau$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The **memory kernel** K(t-œÑ) determines how past states influence present dynamics.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Types of Memory Kernels\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 1. Exponential Kernel (Short-term memory)\n",
    "$$K(\\Delta t) = \\varepsilon e^{-\\gamma \\Delta t}$$\n",
    "- Fast decay\n",
    "- Suitable for systems with finite memory timescale\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Power-Law Kernel (Long-term memory)\n",
    "$$K(\\Delta t) = \\frac{\\varepsilon}{(1 + \\gamma \\Delta t)^\\alpha}$$\n",
    "- Slow decay (algebraic)\n",
    "- Models persistent correlations\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. Oscillatory Kernel (Recurrent memory)\n",
    "$$K(\\Delta t) = \\varepsilon e^{-\\gamma \\Delta t} \\cos(\\omega \\Delta t)$$\n",
    "- Information can \"return\"\n",
    "- Models resonant feedback"
   ]
