    "\n",
    "## Part 2: Quantifying Non-Markovianity\n",
    "\n",
    "### Measure 1: Trace Distance Non-Monotonicity\n",
    "\n",
    "For Markovian dynamics, the trace distance between any two states never increases:\n",
    "$$D(\\rho_1(t), \\rho_2(t)) = \\frac{1}{2}\\|\\rho_1(t) - \\rho_2(t)\\|_1$$\n",
    "\n",
    "should be non-increasing.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Non-Markovian signature**: Distance increases at some times ‚Üí information flows back"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
