    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 3: Intrinsic vs. Environmental Memory\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the **critical distinction** for experimental tests (Paper Section 10).\n",
    "\n",
    "### Environmental Memory\n",
    "\n",
    "**Origin**: System coupled to structured environment\n",
    "$$H = H_S + H_E + H_{SE}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Properties**:\n",
    "1. Memory kernel depends on bath structure\n",
    "2. Can be eliminated by isolation\n",
    "3. **State-dependent** effective dynamics\n",
    "4. Finite-rank process tensors\n",
    "\n",
    "### Intrinsic Spiral-Time Memory\n",
    "\n",
    "**Origin**: Fundamental temporal structure\n",
    "\n",
    "**Properties** (Paper Section 10.1-10.3):\n",
    "1. **State-independent** kernel K(t-œÑ)\n",
    "2. Persists in isolated systems\n",
    "3. Unbounded process tensor rank\n",
    "4. Cannot be eliminated by environmental control"
   ]
