    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 4: Multi-Time Correlations\n",
    "\n",
    "### Two-Time Correlators\n",
    "\n",
    "Define:\n",
    "$$C(t_1, t_2) = \\langle Q(t_1) Q(t_2) \\rangle$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Markovian**: Factorizes for large time separation\n",
    "**Non-Markovian**: Persistent correlations\n",
    "\n",
    "### Three-Time Witnesses\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Leggett-Garg** parameter:\n",
    "$$K_3 = C(t_1,t_2) + C(t_2,t_3) - C(t_1,t_3)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Classical bound: $-3 \\leq K_3 \\leq 1$\n",
    "\n",
    "Violations indicate non-classical temporal correlations."
   ]
